This paper is primarily focused on Federated Learning, which is a subfield of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically looks at the effect of non-identical data distributions on visual classification, which falls under Computer Vision (cs.CV). The proposed solution involves synthesizing datasets and measuring performance, which could also be considered Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses privacy concerns and potential attacks, which could fall under Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper uses statistical measures and proposes a mitigation strategy, which could also be related to Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
